data.text:
Arizona Territory is one of the four starting territories of the California Commonwealth. Its constituent cities and counties seceded from the United States and joined California in forming an independent nation in 2013.

Features[]

Cities and Towns: Phoenix (AZ), Prescott (AZ), Seligman (AZ), Flagstaff (AZ), Tuba City (AZ), Florence (AZ), Gila Bend (AZ), Lake Havasu City (AZ), Blythe (CA), Las Vegas (NV)

Largest City:

Military Bases: Yuma Proving Ground (33 hexes)

Landmarks: Chase Field (Phoenix), Casinos (Las Vegas), Hoover Dam (Las Vegas)

Geographic Features: Sonoran Desert, Mojave Desert, Painted Desert, Verde River, Salt River, Colorado River, Gila River, Dry Gila River Bed, Lake Mead, Lake Havasu

Conservation Areas: Grand Canyon-Parashant National Monument (12 hexes), Grand Canyon National Park (18 hexes), Kofa N.W.R. (23 hexes)

Reservations: Hualapai Indian Reservation (38 hexes)

Roads and Highways: I-18, I-10, I-15, I-17, I-40, Route 60, Route 89, Route 93, Route 95, Route 160

Behind the Scenes[]
